               <p>724. 
               
                  <persName id="t18090920-97-defend993" type="defendantName">
                     THOMAS 
                     RICHARDSON
                  <interp inst="t18090920-97-defend993" type="surname" value="RICHARDSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18090920-97-defend993" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18090920-97-defend993" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for that <rs id="t18090920-97-off561" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18090920-97-off561" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18090920-97-off561" type="offenceSubcategory" value="mail"></interp>
               he being employed as a <rs id="t18090920-97-deflabel562" type="occupation">sorter of letters at the General Post Office</rs>
                     <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18090920-97-defend993 t18090920-97-deflabel562"></join>, on the <rs id="t18090920-97-cd563" type="crimeDate">5th of August</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18090920-97-off561 t18090920-97-cd563"></join> feloniously, knowingly, and wilfully did secrete a certain letter brought to the General Post Office, to be sent from thence by the post to Godstone in the county of Surry to 
                     
                        <persName id="t18090920-97-victim995" type="victimName">
                           John 
                           Hatsell
                        <interp inst="t18090920-97-victim995" type="surname" value="Hatsell"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18090920-97-victim995" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18090920-97-victim995" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18090920-97-off561 t18090920-97-victim995"></join>
                     </persName>
                     
                  , <rs id="t18090920-97-viclabel564" type="occupation">esq</rs>
                     <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18090920-97-victim995 t18090920-97-viclabel564"></join>. containing ten bank post bills value 10 l. each, his property
            </rs>, and several other counts for like offence only varying the manner of charging them.</p>
               <p>The indictment was read by Mr. Roe and the case was stated by Mr. Solicitor general.</p>
